ndidate C's willingness to develop. But we need to ask other agents for info we lack.\n\nWe have missing info: Candidate D's teamwork/communication style beyond arrogance/hot temper (already asked, no info). Maybe we could ask about Candidate D's stress handling or fatigue. Also missing: Candidate B's memory for numbers - we have that it's weak, but maybe ask about any mitigation? But we can't ask about mitigation, only about attributes. Could ask if any other agent has info on Candidate B's stress handling (but we already have that: handles stress very well). Could ask about Candidate C's communication style beyond difficulty and egocentric (maybe ask about teamwork). Already asked earlier, no info.\n\nWe could ask about Candidate D's ability to work in a crew environment, but that's similar to teamwork.\n\nWe could ask about Candidate A's stress handling (already asked, no info). So maybe ask about Candidate D's stress handling or fatigue.\n\nThus we can ask Agent 1 or Agent 2: \"Do you have any information about Candidate D's ability to handle stress and long-duration fatigue?\" That would be a useful missing piece.\n\nAlso we could ask about Candidate B's memory for numbers: \"Do you have any additional information about Candidate B's memory for numbers, such as whether it impacts navigation tasks?\" But we already have \"relatively weak memory for numbers\". That's enough.\n\nWe could also ask about Candidate C's willingness to further education: maybe ask if any info about his professional development plans.\n\nBut the main missing piece for long-distance flights is stress/fatigue for A and D. A we already asked, no info. D we haven't asked. So ask that.\n\nNow we need to produce public message: include reasoning, maybe ask that question, and vote. According to our analysis, we still think Candidate A is best, but we note uncertainty due to lack of stress/fatigue data. We can ask for D's stress/fatigue.\n\nThus public message: summarise evaluation, note missing info, ask question to other agents, and state vote.\n\nNow produce METADATA_JSON with vote.\n\nProceed."}
